{
  "text": "Let us define the series T (s, t; u, v) \u2261 T (u, v) by G(t, z; u, v) = tuvT (tz, t; u, v). The series T (s, t; u, v) is now a formal power series in s and t with coefficients in Q [u, v] . It satisfies is the number of Baxter permutations having m descents, n ascents, i left-to-right maxima and j right-to-left maxima. See Figure 5 for an illustration. The solution of (9) was guessed by the author of [CITATION_1] . The approach presented in this paper allows us to derive it from the functional equation, without having to guess anything. The connection between these two problems is all the more surprising that the author of [CITATION_2] is (Rodney) Baxter, who did not recognize that the numbers he had guessed were related to (Glen) Baxter's permutations... ",
